{ Another move that is possible here is  3...Nc6  However, White may play  4.d4  cxd4  5.Nxd4  and Black gets a slightly different type of position with the knight standing on c6 @@StartBracket@@instead of a pawn on a6@@EndBracket@@. This position happens in the Taimanov Sicilian @@StartBracket@@or Paulsen Sicilian@@EndBracket@@ and requires knowledge of many different lines. But if Black prefers Kan Sicilian positions more, then 3...a6 is really what they need. It's not about the move order, it's more about the type of pawn structure. }
