{ Black controls the e5-square with such a move as well as keeping their dark-squared bishop outside of the pawn chain. }
7. O-O Ne7
{ While Black's dark-squared bishop is located outside the pawn chain, Black may experience some difficulties with the pin of the knight on f6 after Bc1-g5. That's why it's safer to place the knight on e7. However, Ng8-e7 also contains some other ideas that will be revealed later in the analysis. }
8. Qh5 Ng6 9. Be3 Nd7 { The knight on g6 cements Black's defense. } *

