Nc8 14. e5 { To open the d-file and involve the d1-rook into the game. } 14...
Na5 { White has to capture as their other knight is hanging. } 15. Nxa5 Qxa5
16. b3 Bxa4 17. bxa4 O-O
{ Black finishes their development. White doesn't have enough material to initiate a dangerous attack on the kingside. }
18. exd6 Bxe3+ 19. Qxe3 Nxd6
{ An approximately equal position in which White has to trade queens and transition the game into an endgame. The knight on d6 is not worse than a bishop. In case of Bxh7 and Rxd6, White loses the a4-pawn and Black gets the advantage of a better pawn structure. }
