18. Qe2 Ne8 19. Be3 Be6
{ This is a critical position and White has several plans. However, the most modern is Nc3-d5. }
20. Nd5 Bxd5 21. exd5 Nd6
{ The position is quite complicated and both sides have good chances. The d6-knight is the strongest minor piece in this position blocking the d5-pawn and intending to occupy the c4-square or support e5-e4. }
