{ A natural response that allows Black to stay flexible to any plan that White can potentially apply in this position. }
8. a4 b6 9. f4 Bb7 10. Qe2 Nbd7
{ White played Qe2 to threaten to play e4-e5 at some favorable moment. However, Black can play with the d-knight to c5 and relocate the other knight to d7. }
11. f5
{ 11.Kh1  and Bd2 with the idea to play Rae1 are analyzed in the 8.Kh1 line. }
11... e5
{ The best but typical response to f5. This is how Black relieves tension, gains a tempo, and continues their development. }
12. Nf3 Be7 13. Bg5 O-O 14. Nd2 Rfe8
