15. Kh1 d5 16. exd5 e4 17. Ndxe4 Nxe4 18. Bxe7 Nxc3
{ Black wants to take the d5-pawn and exploit the pin. } 19. bxc3 Bxd5 20. c4
Nf6 21. cxd5 Rxe7
{ Black is still one pawn down, but gets compensation due to their piece activity. }
22. Qf3 Qd6 23. c4 Rae8
{ Extra pawn for White, but the position is absolutely equal. The light-squared bishop is bad and its activity is quite restricted with their own pawns. At the same time, Black is able to create a blockade with their knight while supported with the f7-f6 move. The blockade can be set up either on e5 or c5 and of course, Black's queen activity cannot be ignored. }
