{ to secure the e5-square and potentially attack through the c-file. } 13. Qe2
Bd7 14. Rb1
{ Just a helpful move in the future as it activates the rook for a potential endgame and adds pressure to the b7-pawn. }
14... Rae8 { Intending to force through e5-e4. } 15. Qe4 f5 16. Qh4 b6
{ Prophylaxis! This move is required to secure the b-pawn and the c5-square in some lines. Black is going to create a light-squared bind with Nc6-a5-c4, while there is no clear continuation for White's attack. The Bc1xh6 sacrifice doesn't work as Black can always get one of their major pieces to the 7th rank and defend the king. }
