4... cxd4 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. cxd4 e6
{ 6...e6 is one of the main options for Black.  6...d6  is another popular option, for example. But if Black decides to follow the Kan Sicilian, they may reach this position with an absolutely different move order. That's why it's highly recommended to stick to the same strategy every time. A high-level player, of course, may learn several possible lines here and vary them from time to time. }
