1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5. c4
{ Maroczy Bind is considered to be one of the strongest continuations against the Kan Sicilian. }
5... Nf6
{ Usually we start with Qc7 to secure the e5-square, but in this position, White can't play e4-e5. Black replies with Qa5+ and captures the pawn for free. }
