{ Black should definitely pin the knight here if White allows it. The idea is to trade. }
8. Qd3 Nc6 9. Nxc6 dxc6 10. Bg2 e5 { Makes White's light-squared bishop bad. }
11. O-O O-O
{ Black doesn't have any bad pieces, and has greater control of the center because the c6-pawn prevents White from posting the knight to  d5  . If  12.a3  Black has the option to retreat the bishop to e7 or, after  12...Rd8  reposition the bishop via c5 to d4. }
